  "prompt": "What are the best one-minute life hacks?",
  "response": "Here are some quick and useful one-minute life hacks:\n\n1. Personal Organization\n- Set a timer for 5 minutes to quickly tidy a room\n- Use vertical storage to maximize space\n- Fold clothes using the KonMari method for more compact storage\n\n2. Time Management\n- Use the two-minute rule: if a task takes less than two minutes, do it immediately\n- Plan your day the night before\n- Keep a running to-do list\n\n3. Technology\n- Charge your phone faster by putting it in airplane mode\n- Use voice-to-text for quick messaging\n- Clear your browser cache to improve performance\n\n4. Kitchen\n- Use a stapler to seal chip bags\n- Microwave lemons for 15 seconds to get more juice\n- Use a wooden spoon to prevent pots from boiling over\n\n5. Health & Wellness\n- Do quick stretches while waiting\n- Practice deep breathing for stress relief\n- Drink a glass of water first thing in the morning\n\n6. Money\n- Round up purchases and save the difference\n- Unsubscribe from marketing emails to reduce impulse spending\n- Check for price matching before purchasing\n\n7. Miscellaneous\n- Keep a spare phone charger in different locations\n- Use binder clips to organize cables\n- Keep a spare emergency kit in your car",
